This paper is about image super-resolution using deep learning techniques, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also proposes a new network architecture that utilizes attention mechanisms, which is a popular topic in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper deals with multiscale feature extraction, which is relevant to multimedia (cs.MM) and neural networks (cs.NE) sub-categories.
